### 1. API Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

###

### 2. Login as Admin to get Security Token (JWT)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "password": "Password123!"
}

###

### Save Token from the Login Request response to a variable
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

###

### 3. Fetch All Projects (Public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/projects

###

### 4. Fetch Single Project by ID (Public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/projects/1

###

### 5. Attempt to Create Project WITHOUT Token (Should Fail with 401)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Hack Attack Project",
    "description": "Should not allow unauthorized creation.",
    "technologies": ["Malware", "Exploits"]
}

###

### 6. Create Project WITH Token (Should Succeed with 201)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Social Network App",
    "description": "A fully functional chat and networking application.",
    "technologies": ["React", "Express", "Socket.io"],
    "imageUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1522071820081-009f0129c71c?auto=format&fit=crop&w=600&q=80",
    "githubUrl": "https://github.com"
}

###

### 7. Update Project (Should Succeed with 200)
# Updates the template project (ID: 1)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/projects/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "Updated Portfolio Site",
    "description": "An incredibly secure, updated, and state-of-the-art developer portfolio."
}

###

### 8. Delete Project (Should Succeed with 200)
# Deletes the template project (ID: 1)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/projects/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}